div.p:
69. The four steamers named below which have sailed from Genoa for New York this
                    morning carried the following numbers of American and alien passengers coming
                    from all parts of Europe: Excalibur May 2, Americans 57,
                    aliens 27; Manhattan May 4, Americans 317, aliens 504;
                        Exeter May 16, Americans 81, aliens 49; Washington May 19, Americans 483, aliens 588, making a
                    total of 938 American citizens and 1,168 aliens.
